Question Generation System (QuGen)
Overview

QuGen is an AI-powered question generation system designed to automatically generate exam-oriented questions from input text or images.
The project supports multiple question formats commonly used in academic evaluations.

This system is useful for:

Teachers and educators

Exam preparation tools

AI-based learning platforms

Features

Automatic question generation from text

Supports multiple question formats:

One-mark questions

Six-mark questions

Twelve-mark questions

Image-based text extraction

Custom question formatting

Modular and extensible codebase

Project Structure
qugen/
│
├── app.py                 # Main application entry point
├── extraction.py          # Text extraction logic
├── check.py               # Utility / testing script
├── qformat.py             # Question formatting utilities
│
├── one_mark.py            # One-mark question generator
├── six_marks.py           # Six-mark question generator
├── twelve_marks.py        # Twelve-mark question generator
│
├── image.png              # Sample input image
├── requirements2.txt      # Project dependencies
├── .env                   # Environment variables
│
├── venv/                  # Virtual environment
└── __pycache__/           # Python cache files

Installation
1. Clone the Repository
git clone https://github.com/<your-username>/qugen.git
cd qugen

2. Create and Activate Virtual Environment (Windows)
python -m venv venv
venv\Scripts\activate

3. Install Dependencies
pip install -r requirements2.txt

Configuration

Create a .env file in the root directory and add your API keys or configuration values:

API_KEY=your_api_key_here

Usage

Run the main application:

python app.py


You can modify input text, image files, or question formats as required in the respective modules.

Customization

Modify one_mark.py, six_marks.py, or twelve_marks.py to adjust question difficulty

Extend extraction.py for advanced OCR or text processing

Update qformat.py to change output structure

Tech Stack

Python 3.x

NLP / LLM-based processing

OCR (for image input)

Modular Python architecture

Future Enhancements

Web UI for question generation

Support for PDF input

Difficulty-level control

Batch question generation

Export to PDF or DOCX

